NORMALISED EXTRACT
Rules and variants
- Replace numbers divisible by 3 with "fizz".
- Replace numbers divisible by 5 with "buzz".
- Replace numbers divisible by both 3 and 5 with "fizzbuzz" (i.e., divisible by 15).
- Variations: add other divisibility rules (e.g., 7) or trigger on digit containment (e.g., a number containing digit 5 triggers the 5 rule).

Implementation patterns
- Basic loop pattern: for n from 1 to N, test divisibility and print the appropriate token or the number.
  - Check divisibility by 15 first: if (n % 15 === 0) output "fizzbuzz".
  - Else if (n % 3 === 0) output "fizz".
  - Else if (n % 5 === 0) output "buzz".
- Alternative pattern: build result string by concatenation: let out = ''; if (n % 3 === 0) out += 'fizz'; if (n % 5 === 0) out += 'buzz'; if (out === '') out = String(n); output out.
- Functional pattern: map over a generated range and produce array of tokens using modular tests.

Edge cases and alternatives
- Zero: 0 is divisible by any non-zero integer; pattern yields "fizzbuzz" for 0.
- Negative numbers: divisibility rules apply; use absolute value or define domain to positive integers.
- Large N: use streaming/output buffering rather than building huge in-memory arrays.
- Interview use: simple problem used to screen for basic coding ability; consider adding constraints (no modulo operator, single-pass, O(1) memory) for increased difficulty.

SUPPLEMENTARY DETAILS
Technical specifications
- Divisibility: integer n divisible by k iff n % k === 0 in languages with modulo operator.
- Combined divisibility: check for least common multiple (LCM) of divisors (LCM(3,5)=15) to detect "fizzbuzz".

Implementation tips
- Order checks from most specific (LCM) to least specific to avoid incorrect outputs.
- Concatenation approach generalises to arbitrary rule sets without needing LCM checks.
- For digit-containment rules: convert to string and check includes() or implement digit scanning for performance.

