API / Patterns
- Loop pseudo-signature: for (let n = start; n <= end; n++) { ... }
- Divisibility check signature: isDivisible(n: integer, k: integer) -> boolean where isDivisible returns (n % k === 0).
- Concatenate pattern: let out = ''; if (isDivisible(n,3)) out += 'fizz'; if (isDivisible(n,5)) out += 'buzz'; output out || String(n).

TROUBLESHOOTING
- Unexpected blank outputs: ensure output fallback uses string conversion of number.
- Performance issues for very large ranges: avoid creating arrays of size N; stream results or process in chunks.

